# Misfits — trait display strings for Pets perk tree

trait-name-FiremanCarry = Fireman Carry
trait-description-FiremanCarry = You can pick people up and drag them without losing speed.

trait-name-N14PetDogCompanion = Dog Companion
trait-description-N14PetDogCompanion =
    You have a loyal dog companion that follows and obeys you.
    A dog from the wastes has taken a liking to you. Whether you found it wandering the ruins or raised it yourself, it'll stay by your side no matter what.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14PetBrahmin = Brahmin
trait-description-N14PetBrahmin =
    You have a brahmin that follows you into the wastes.
    Two-headed and stubborn, this beast of burden plods loyally at your heels. Won't win any beauty contests, but it'll carry what needs carrying.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14PetMirelurk = Mirelurk
trait-description-N14PetMirelurk =
    You have a mirelurk that follows and (mostly) obeys you.
    How you tamed this irradiated crustacean is anyone's guess. It snaps at everyone else, but not you. Useful.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14PetRadChicken = Rad Chicken
trait-description-N14PetRadChicken =
    You have a rad chicken that follows you around.
    Clucks, pecks, glows faintly. A loyal, if useless, companion. Don't eat it.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14PetCat = Cat
trait-description-N14PetCat =
    You have a cat that tolerates your presence.
    It doesn't listen, it doesn't help, but it's yours and that's enough.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14PetCatBlack = Black Cat
trait-description-N14PetCatBlack =
    You have a black cat that tolerates your presence.
    A void-colored feline that keeps to the shadows and judges everyone equally.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14PetCatBrownTabby = Brown Tabby Cat
trait-description-N14PetCatBrownTabby =
    You have a brown tabby cat that tolerates your presence.
    A dusty-striped wasteland cat that looks like it has seen every ruin on the map.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14PetCatCalico = Calico Cat
trait-description-N14PetCatCalico =
    You have a calico cat that tolerates your presence.
    Patchwork fur, stubborn attitude, and exactly zero respect for your authority.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14PetCatGingerTabby = Ginger Tabby Cat
trait-description-N14PetCatGingerTabby =
    You have a ginger tabby cat that tolerates your presence.
    Warm-colored, loud, and probably already planning something obnoxious.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14PetCatGrayTabby = Gray Tabby Cat
trait-description-N14PetCatGrayTabby =
    You have a gray tabby cat that tolerates your presence.
    A weathered little survivor with the sort of face that says it has seen too much.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14PetCatMela = Mela Cat
trait-description-N14PetCatMela =
    You have a mela cat that tolerates your presence.
    A melanistic cat with a sleek coat and a habit of disappearing into the dark.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14PetCatOcicat = Ocicat
trait-description-N14PetCatOcicat =
    You have an ocicat that tolerates your presence.
    Wild-looking stripes, domesticated attitude, and just enough menace to be interesting.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14PetCatSiamese = Siamese Cat
trait-description-N14PetCatSiamese =
    You have a siamese cat that tolerates your presence.
    Slender, talkative, and convinced that it runs the settlement.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14PetCatSphinx = Sphinx Cat
trait-description-N14PetCatSphinx =
    You have a sphinx cat that tolerates your presence.
    Hairless, strange, and unsettlingly warm to the touch.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14PetCatTortoiseshell = Tortoiseshell Cat
trait-description-N14PetCatTortoiseshell =
    You have a tortoiseshell cat that tolerates your presence.
    A mottled-fur troublemaker with a reputation for getting exactly what it wants.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14PetCatWhite = White Cat
trait-description-N14PetCatWhite =
    You have a white cat that tolerates your presence.
    Pale fur, bright eyes, and the sort of innocence that feels suspicious.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14PetCentaur = Centaur (Supermutant Only)
trait-description-N14PetCentaur =
    You have a centaur that follows you. (Work in Progress)
    A grotesque FEV-warped creature bonded to you through mutation and misery. Only another mutant could earn such trust.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-MisfitsPetEyebotTribe = Treyebot
trait-description-MisfitsPetEyebotTribe =
    You have an eyebot that you've "fixed" up for the tribe.
    A military eyebot sporting an animal skull. Its laser rusted over long ago, but you've strapped a knife to it.
    (The trait creates a ghost role for another player. There is no guarantee that someone takes it.)

trait-name-N14RidingPerk = Riding
trait-description-N14RidingPerk =
    You know how to handle wasteland motorcycles.
    Old engines, bad roads, and improvised frames are familiar enough that you can keep a bike moving without wrecking yourself.

trait-name-LanguageTribalGeneral = Tribal Language
trait-description-LanguageTribalGeneral = You can understand and speak the local Tribal language. Were you from the Tribe?

trait-name-N14TribalAccent = Tribal Accent
trait-description-N14TribalAccent = Ya be, or musta been membaa de tribe. Bird tribe be not gawnta ondastan ya tong.
